  "readme_html": "\n        \n          <p><img src=\"https://ollama.com/assets/library/codegeex4/b3a2d858-363f-4a6c-a9c7-056f74bc2910\" alt=\"logo.jpg\"/></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note: this model requires <a href=\"https://github.com/ollama/ollama/releases/tag/v0.2.0\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ollama 0.2</a> or later.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>CodeGeeX4 is an open multilingual code generation model continually trained on the <a href=\"https://ollama.com/library/glm4\" rel=\"nofollow\">GLM-4-9B</a>, significantly enhancing its code generation capabilities.</p>\n\n<p>CodeGeeX4-ALL-9B has achieved highly competitive performance on public benchmarks, such as BigCodeBench and NaturalCodeBench. It is currently the most powerful code generation model with less than 10B parameters, even surpassing much larger general-purpose models, achieving the best balance in terms of inference speed and model performance.</p>\n\n<h1>References</h1>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/THUDM/CodeGeeX4\" rel=\"nofollow\">GitHub</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://huggingface.co/THUDM/codegeex4-all-9b\" rel=\"nofollow\">Hugging Face</a></p>\n\n        \n      ",
